Met a teacher on his way to making $20k+/month passively in retirement. He committed to building wealth, met people who pointed him the right direction, picked a strategy, picked a market, and TOOK ACTION!
.
Love hearing and sharing success stories of people who commit to building wealth through Real Estate, especially regular people. There's so many stories like this! 
.
Outsiders have no idea what's possible when you commit to investing in RE for the long haul. Most people have no idea what sort of life they can create for themselves. It's incredible what is possible for someone who combines knowledge and action.
.

Before pics at the end. Finished this ADU project and it's ready to rent! Converted a living room from the main house and the attached 1 car garage into a 1bed/1bath 500 sq ft unit. Also got to reuse a fridge from a different project. Took about 5 months from permit submittal to construction completion. Spent about 95k. Adds even more value to the property. Will rent for 2k/month. As always, more projects to come. Onward
.
